{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2015}} {{Infobox organization | name = Christians in the Visual Arts | native_name = | named_after = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | map = | map_size = | map_alt = | map_caption = | map2 = | map2_size = | map2_alt = | map2_caption = | abbreviation = CIVA | motto = Serious art. Serious faith. | predecessor = | merged = | successor = | formation = {{start date|1979}} | founder = | founding_location = | extinction = <!-- use {{end date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | merger = | type = | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | status = | purpose = | headquarters = | location = | coords = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|display=inline,title}} --> | region = | services = | products = | methods = | fields = | membership = | membership_year = | language = | owner = <!-- or | owners = --> | sec_gen = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | board_of_directors = | key_people = [[Sandra Bowden]] | main_organ = | parent_organization = | subsidiaries = | secessions = | affiliations = | budget = | budget_year = | revenue = | revenue_year = | disbursements = | expenses = | expenses_year = | endowment = | staff = | staff_year = | volunteers = | volunteers_year = | slogan = | mission = | website = {{URL|http://civa.org/}} | remarks = | formerly = | footnotes = }} '''Christians in the Visual Arts''' ('''CIVA''') is an American visual arts organization working to enhance and explore the relationship between Christian faith and the visual arts.<ref>{{cite news|title=Art Connections: Christians in the Visual Arts (CIVA)|url=http://www.wheaton.edu/Academics/Departments/Art/Connections/CIVA|accessdate=9 April 2015|publisher=Wheaton College}}</ref><ref name="Sherman">{{cite book|last1=Sherman|first1=Amy|title=Kingdom Calling: Vocational Stewardship for the Common Good|date=2011|isbn=0830838090}}<!--|accessdate=9 April 2015--></ref> It was founded in 1979.<ref name=curatormag>{{cite news|title=Art as Hospitality|url=http://www.curatormagazine.com/civa/art-as-hospitality/|accessdate=9 April 2015|publisher=Curator Magazine|date=23 March 2015}}</ref>
Gallery instructor Jeremy Hamilton-Arnold describes CIVA's work as "Many of the artists involved [in CIVA] are making art worth showing, sharing, and talking about."<ref name="HamiltonArnold">{{cite web|last1=Hamilton-Arnold|first1=Jeremy|title=Bad Christian Art: "Excuse me while I go throw up and rock myself in a corner"|url=http://www.patheos.com/blogs/poptheology/2013/09/bad-christian-art/#ixzz3WqCTZQJ0|website=Patheos|accessdate=9 April 2015}}</ref> It publishes the ''Seen'' magazine,<ref name="curatormag" /> and co-curates and co-sponsors traveling art exhibitions.<ref name=Pellegrini>{{cite news|last1=Pelligrini|first1=Roseanne|title=Exhibit Sets the Table for a Spiritual Feast|url=http://www.bc.edu/publications/chronicle/FeaturesNewsTopstories/2014/news/bc-exhibit-sets-the-table-for-a-spiritual-feast.html?cq_ck=1417725148086|accessdate=9 April 2015|publisher=Boston College Chronicle|date=4 December 2014}}</ref><ref name=Golden>{{cite news|last1=Golden|first1=Karris|title=Westminster marks anniversary with art exhibit, other events|url=http://wcfcourier.com/lifestyles/faith-and-values/westminster-marks-anniversary-with-art-exhibit-other-events/article_29be316c-b99c-5069-affa-6447387c761d.html|accessdate=5 May 2015|publisher=Waterloo Cedar Falls Courier|date=24 April 2015}}</ref>
